videos.description: Miles Bridges is making his name known in his first game with Michigan State thanks to this awesome reverse dunk to get the Spartans off and running early.
videos.headline: Bridges introducing himself with awesome dunk

videos.description: Alvin Ellis III shows off the passing skills with the one-handed dish to to Kenny Goins for a two-handed flush for Michigan State.
videos.headline: Sweet dish leads to massive Goins dunk

videos.description: ARIZ Lauri Markkanen made Three Point Jumper.
videos.headline: 7 foot freshman Lauri Markkanen shows off his range

videos.description: ARIZ Kobi Simmons made Three Point Jumper.
videos.headline: Kobi Simmons pull up three gives Arizona first lead of the game

videos.description: Miles Bridges already has a highlight-reel dunk in the game for Michigan State and this time throws a rocket pass to Nick Ward for the powerful two-hand slam.
videos.headline: Bridges' sweet pass leads to vicious two-hand dunk

videos.description: Arizona head coach Sean Miller talks about the first half success of freshman Kobi Simmons
videos.headline: Arizona head coach Sean Miller talks about the first half success of freshman Kobi Simmons

videos.description: Miles Bridges does his best Dr. J impersonation with the reverse layup down the baseline for Michigan State.
videos.headline: Bridges goes up-and-under for dazzling reverse layup

videos.description: MSU Miles Bridges made Dunk. Assisted by Kenny Goins.
videos.headline: Bridges adds to the highlight reel with alley-oop finish

videos.description: Miles Bridges does this one by himself, spinning around his defender to get in the lane and throws down the monstrous one-hand dunk.
videos.headline: Bridges with the sweet spin and hammer dunk

videos.description: MSU Matt McQuaid made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Alvin Ellis III.
videos.headline: Matt McQuaid three brings Michigan state level with Arizona

videos.description: The Miles Bridges show continues for Michigan State when Alvin Ellis III throws up the alley-oop to Bridges for a dunk that leaves the rim shaking.
videos.headline: Bridges can't stop throwing down nasty dunks
Michigan State looking to take momentum with big three
Arizona grabs 3 point lead in final 40 seconds

videos.description: MSU Lourawls Nairn Jr. made Three Point Jumper.
videos.headline: Michigan State hits game tying three with 7 seconds left

videos.description: In the final seconds of a tie game, Kadeem Allen cuts to the hoop and scores the tough layup to win the game for Arizona over Michigan State.
videos.headline: Allen the hero for Arizona with last-second layup

videos.description: Arizona head coach Sean Miller talks about Kadeem Allen and his efforts to capture the win
videos.headline: Arizona head coach Sean Miller talks about Kadeem Allen and his efforts to capture the win
